# ⏰ Digital Clock Using 8051 Microcontroller and LCD

This project demonstrates a real-time digital clock built using the **8051 microcontroller (AT89C51)** and a **16x2 LCD display**. The clock displays the current time in the `hh:mm:ss` format and updates every second using embedded C logic.

---

## 📌 Objective

To design and implement a basic digital clock using the 8051 microcontroller, showcasing time management and LCD interfacing in embedded systems.

---

## ⚙️ Working Explanation

- The microcontroller counts seconds, minutes, and hours.
- Time is displayed continuously on the LCD in the format `hh:mm:ss`.
- A software-based delay simulates one-second time increments.
- The display updates in real-time, cycling from `00:00:00` to `23:59:59`.

---

## 🧠 Features

- Real-time clock display  
- 24-hour format  
- LCD interfacing using 16x2 display  
- Written in Embedded C

---

## 🖥️ Circuit Components

- AT89C51 Microcontroller  
- 16x2 LCD Display  
- Power Supply  
- Crystal Oscillator (11.0592 MHz recommended)  
- Resistors, Capacitors, and Reset circuitry

---

## 📜 Code Snippet (Main Loop)
```c
while(1) {
    display_time();
    update_time();
}# 8051-Digital-Clock-Using
